&lt;p&gt;The project was made in Xilinx’s Vivado using VHDL. The requirements were to make a state machine that implemented the following equalization algorithm for black and white imagines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;delta_value = max_pixel_value - min_pixel_value
shift_level = (8-floor(log2(delta_value + 1)
temp_level = (current_pixel_value - min_pixel_value) &amp;lt;&amp;lt; shift_level
new_pixel_value = min(255, temp_pixel)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I used a Mealy state machine to create the circuit. It was synthesized with a clock period of 15ns and works pre and post synthesis. Since optimization was not a requirement for the project, I valued code readability higher than using a low amount of states in the state machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can read the code &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chiarabia/Progetto-Reti-Logiche-2021/blob/main/progetto%20reti.vhd&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can read a report of the project (in italian)&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chiarabia/Progetto-Reti-Logiche-2021/blob/main/report.pdf&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hermann Snake]]></title><description><![CDATA[Hermann Snake is a game I made during April 2021 Black and White game jam. The theme of the jam was to create a game completely in black and…]]></description><link>https://chiarabianchimani.it/hermann-snake/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://chiarabianchimani.it/hermann-snake/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 01 Apr 2021 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;
