&lt;p&gt;The requirement of the project was the implementation in C of a text editor with the commands add, delete, undo, redo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project purpose was to pass a test suite with strict space and time requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I used lists as the general data structure. For the redo and undo commands I took inspiration from the command design pattern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find the project &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chiarabia/ProgettoAPI2020&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Composer]]></title><description><![CDATA[This project was made in collaboration with Andrea Franchini. The project started with the idea of giving robots, and thus the people…]]></description><link>https://chiarabianchimani.it/Composer/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://chiarabianchimani.it/Composer/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 01 Sep 2020 22:12:03 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;This project was made in collaboration with &lt;a href=&quot;https://andreafranchini.com&quot;&gt;Andrea Franchini&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project started with the idea of giving robots, and thus the people programming them, a quick way to give feedback in a human way.
This was achieved with a easy-to-use webapp where the user can create a musical score, activate motors and LEDS and then generate JSOn or Arduino code with their creation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The webapp is made with React and Redux and by using Typescript. It was made with ease of extensibility in mind. You can read more about it in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/QUB3X/composer/blob/master/Report.pdf&quot;&gt;report&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is the live &lt;a href=&quot;https://composer.netlify.app&quot;&gt;demo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/QUB3X/composer&quot;&gt;code&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Software Engineering Project]]></title><description><![CDATA[This project was my thesis for my Bachelor degree. It was complementary to my Software Engineering class. I made it in collaboration with…]]></description><link>https://chiarabianchimani.it/Software Engineering Project/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://chiarabianchimani.it/Software Engineering Project/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 28 Jul 2020 22:40:32 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;This project was my thesis for my Bachelor degree. It was complementary to my Software Engineering class. I made it in collaboration with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/MarcelloMatteoDeclich&quot;&gt;@MarcelloMatteoDeclich&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/vittoriodani&quot;&gt;@vittoriodani&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project consisted in the Java implementation of the tabletop game Santorini.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We were required to use the MVC pattern, create socket connectivity, CLI and GUI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I worked at the entirety of the GUI and also in particular in the implementation and testing of the logic of the game.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find the project &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chiarabia/Soft_Eng_BoardGame_2020&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. This project is not exactly the same as the one presented as the thesis, since the latter had copyrighted material of the game. &lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>